President Trump spoke to the media after visiting the El Paso Regional Communications Center in Texas. He described the love and respect he received during his visit and mentioned meeting with hospital staff, doctors, and nurses who have done an incredible job. The President also praised Private First Class Oakley for his heroic actions. When asked about his criticism of Vice President Biden, Senator Brown, Mayor Whaley, and the media, President Trump stated that they shouldn't be politicking on a day of healing and unity. He mentioned that Senator Brown and Mayor Whaley were impressed by the hospital's response to the shooting but later criticized him. President Trump emphasized that they were dishonest and failed as political candidates. The President concluded by mentioning his plan to meet with brave individuals.